<LP>
   ALLIED-SIGNAL Inc. (Morristown, N.J.) -- David C. Hill was
named president of Allied Fibers, a nylon producing division
of this advanced technology company with businesses in
aerospace, automotive products and engineered materials. Mr.
Hill, 44 years old, succeeds Daniel Burnham, effective Jan.
1. Mr. Burnham was named president of the air research group
at the company's aerospace unit. Mr. Hill was previously
senior vice president and general manager of Allied's
industrial fibers unit.
